{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Database Migration Linter",
  "description": "Analyzes Supabase database migrations for destructive operations, performance issues, and best practices compliance. Warns about dropping columns/tables, suggests indexes for foreign keys, and enforces naming conventions.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "supabase/migrations/*.sql"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are a database migration expert reviewing a Supabase SQL migration file. Analyze the migration for:\n\n1. **Destructive Operations**: Check for DROP TABLE, DROP COLUMN, ALTER COLUMN (type changes), TRUNCATE operations that could cause data loss\n2. **Performance Issues**: \n   - Missing indexes on foreign key columns\n   - Large table alterations without proper considerations\n   - Inefficient query patterns in migration scripts\n3. **Best Practices**:\n   - Proper naming conventions for tables, columns, indexes, constraints\n   - Use of transactions where appropriate\n   - Rollback considerations\n   - Comments and documentation\n\nProvide specific recommendations and warnings. If destructive operations are found, clearly highlight the risks and suggest safer alternatives where possible."
  }
}